@*
1. Add an observable array, items, to MyApp. This should be a "public" property.
2. Create an initialize() function that creates Item objects for years from 2010 to 2020 and appends them to the observable array. Call it and apply bindings.
3. In the table, create a foreach binding.
    - the first cell should have the index of the item, 1-based.
    - the second cell should have the year
    - the third cell should have <a href="javascript:;">Remove</a> (wired later)
   Test bindings.
4. In the VM create an addFirst method that adds an item at the beginning of items array (with first year - 1 or 2010 if there are no items). Mind the way the items array is referenced.
   Wire it to the Add first button.
5. In the VM create a removeFirst and removeLast methods.
   Wire them to the respective buttons.
   Add binding to make the remove buttons disabled when there're no items in the items array.
6. In the main VM create create a remove() method that removes the specified item.
   Wire it to the <a> in the last cell. Note that the method is in the parent (at the same time root VM). Try to adapt binding to the first and the second case.
7. Extend the remove() method so that it requires shift + click.
8. Add clear() method that removes all items, wire it to the respective button.
*@

